>\n    <tr>\n      <td>First 13 weeks</td>\n      <td>Under 25</td>\n      <td>£56.25</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>First 13 weeks</td>\n      <td>25 or over</td>\n      <td>£71.00</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>From 14 weeks</td>\n      <td>Work Related Activity Group</td>\n      <td>Up to £99.15</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>From 14 weeks</td>\n      <td>Support Group</td>\n      <td>Up to £105.05</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>How much you get depends on your circumstances (eg <a href=\"/employment-support-allowance/eligibility\" title=\"Income\">income</a> and the type of <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> you qualify for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>contribution-based <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> - usually you get this if you&rsquo;ve got enough <a href=\"/national-insurance\" title=\"National Insurance\">National Insurance contributions</a> (<abbr title=\"National Insurance contributions\">NICs</abbr>) </li>\n  <li>Income-based <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> - usually you get this if you&rsquo;re on a low income or you don&rsquo;t have enough <abbr title=\"National Insurance contributions\">NICs</abbr></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/benefits-adviser\" title=\"Benefits adviser\">benefits adviser</a> to work out how much you can get.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Work-related support and interviews</h2>\n\n<p>After 13 weeks of <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> you&rsquo;ll be put into a group. </p>\n\n<p>In the Work-Related Activity Group - you&rsquo;ll be expected to go to regular interviews with an adviser. The adviser can help with things like job goals, improving your skills, work-related issues. Your <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> may stop if you don&rsquo;t take part in these interviews. </p>\n\n<p>In the Support Group - you don&rsquo;t have to go to interviews, but you can ask to talk to a personal adviser if you want to. You&rsquo;re usually in this group if your illness or disability severely limits what you can do. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Contribution-based <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> lasts 1 year if you’re in the Work-Related Activity Group (you may be moved onto income-based <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> after this time).</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances are paid <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"how to have your benefits paid\">into an account</a>, eg your bank account.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>From April 2013 a <a href=\"/benefit-cap\" title=\"benefit cap\">cap</a> (limit) will be put on the total amount of benefit that most people aged 16 to 64 can get. The cap won’t affect you if you’re in the Support Group.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/employment-support-allowance/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<p>You may get Employment and Support Allowance (<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>) if your illness or disability affects your ability to work and you&rsquo;re: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>under <a href=\"/state-pension\" title=\"State Pension\">State Pension</a> age </li>\n  <li>not getting Statutory Sick Pay or Statutory Maternity Pay and you haven&rsquo;t gone back to work</li>\n  <li>not getting Job Seeker&rsquo;s Allowance </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can apply for <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> if you&rsquo;re employed, self-employed or unemployed. </p>\n\n<p>You may get <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> if you&rsquo;ve lived or work abroad and paid enough National \nInsurance (UK or equivalent). </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/benef