 them about how to do this yourself.</p>\n\n<h3>Employment on Trial</h3>\n\n<p>Employment on Trial allows you to leave a job and start claiming <a href=\"/jobseekers-allowance\" title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">Jobseeker’s Allowance</a> again without this affecting your benefit (unless you&rsquo;re sacked or leave because of misconduct).</p>\n\n<p>You must have worked more than 16 hours a week for between 4 and 12 weeks before leaving the job.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/moving-from-benefits-to-work/starting-your-own-business","slug":"starting-your-own-business","order":4,"title":"Starting your own business","body":"<p>Your <a href=\"/contact-jobcentre-plus\" title=\"contact Jobcentre Plus\">Jobcentre Plus</a> adviser can tell you about help you can get to start up your own business.</p>\n\n<h2>New Enterprise Allowance</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve been getting <a href=\"/jobseekers-allowance\" title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">Jobseeker’s Allowance</a> for 3 months and can show that you have a business idea that could work, you can apply for New Enterprise Allowance.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll be given a business mentor, who will provide advice and support on becoming self-employed and setting up your business.</p>\n\n<p>After 6 months, you could also get financial support including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a weekly allowance worth up to £1,274 over 26 weeks</li>\n  <li>a loan of up to £1,000 to help with start-up costs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Enterprise Clubs</h2>\n\n<p>Anyone who’s unemployed can join an Enterprise Club. You’ll be able to share experiences and get help from other people who want to become self-employed, as well as local business people and advisers.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/moving-from-benefits-to-work/help-for-parents-and-carers","slug":"help-for-parents-and-carers","order":5,"title":"Help for parents and carers","body":"<p>Your <a href=\"/contact-jobcentre-plus\" title=\"contact Jobcentre Plus\">Jobcentre Plus</a> adviser can tell you abou