orded in a &lsquo;jobseeker&rsquo;s agreement&rsquo;. You&rsquo;ll normally have a review meeting every 2 weeks to check if you&rsquo;re doing the things in your agreement. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you don’t attend your interview or your review meetings this will delay your <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> payment and may mean you won’t get any <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> at all.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re a single parent</h2>\n\n<p>Find out how being a lone parent may affect your Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance and what help is available.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@benefits/documents/digitalasset/dg_199922.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Jobseeker's Allowance and flexibilities for lone parents' (PDF, 85KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Jobseeker’s Allowance and flexibilities for lone parents’ (PDF, 85KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How you could lose your benefit</h2>\n\n<p>You could lose your Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance for up to 13 weeks if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t attend an adviser interview</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t take compulsory steps that will help you find work, eg by attending a training course when you&rsquo;re told to</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t apply for or don&rsquo;t accept a place on an employment programme or  training scheme that you&rsquo;re told about</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t attend or take part in an employment programme or  training scheme, or leave voluntarily</li>\n  <li>lose  your place on an employment programme or  training scheme because of misconduct</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You could lose your Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance for up to 3  years if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t apply for a job that your adviser tells you about</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t accept a suitable job offer</li>\n  <li>leave a job voluntarily, or lose your job because of misconduct</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t take